Nusa, Dan, Enoh, and Joe, good evening!

I am sending 3 files for the "Guide to Produce Scoping Literature Reviews U=
sing AI Tools."

  *
Parts 1-3 file (47 pages) - this file includes the entire guide for the sco=
ping reviews.
     *
Dan, please post this file for all TIM students to access.
     *
Joe, please use the AI tools we spoke about this morning to produce assessm=
ents for the Parts 1-3 file and send them to me. I have not been able to wo=
rk on the instructions you kindly sent me this morning. Therefore, I need y=
ou to do these assessments for me once again. This time we wil do a formal =
comparison on the quality of the assessments
     *
Enoh, we will not produce a video or podcast for the Parts 1-3 file - it is=
 too big.
  *
Part 2 file (28 pages) - Enoh, please produce the video and podcast for thi=
s file first
  *
Part 1 file (15 pages) - Enoh, please produce the video and podcast for thi=
s file after we are convinced that the video and podcast for Part 2 works o=
k

I am departing the Nicol building shortly to get something to eat. Starved!

Once I get home, I'll start working on the guide for producing systematic l=
iterature reviews. Not sure how much the Parts 1-3 file for the systematic =
review will be different from the Parts 1-3 file of the scoping review. Reg=
ardless, we have to keep the two types of reviews in different locations in=
 the website.

Nusa, it will be great if you examined file with Parts 1-3 again to ensure =
that I properly incorporated your suggestions.

Let's get this done asap!

Thank you all!

Tony B








